body:
@Hgit007 You can set the size of images in the configuration file using `INPUT_SIZE` flag, it is not limited to 256x265 only (please follow the readme file instructions)
- Q1: We do downsample/upsample the mask to match the size of your training set i.e. `INPUT_SIZE`
- Q2: You need to download an external mask dataset and create a `.flist` file much like your training set. Use `TRAIN_MASK_FLIST` flag in the configuration to set the path to your mask dataset file list. Every iteration, we randomly sample from the training set and the mask dataset!
